"title": "2009: Jesus Christ, anger of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2009",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ's controlled emotion arising from his unswerving opposition to evil and his determination to eradicate it.</p>\n<h2>Causes of Jesus Christ's anger</h2>\n<h3>Petty legalism in religious observance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:3\">MAT 15:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:1-Matt23:4\">MAT 23:1–23:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:4-Mark3:5\">MRK 3:4–3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Attempts to prevent access to him</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:14\">MRK 10:14</a></p>\n<h3>People leading others into sin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:6-Matt18:7\">MAT 18:6–18:7</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:42\">MRK 9:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:1-Luke17:2\">LUK 17:1–17:2</a></p>\n<h2>Demonstrations of Jesus Christ's anger</h2>\n<h3>Purging the temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:12-Matt21:13\">MAT 21:12–21:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:15-Mark11:17\">MRK 11:15–11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:45-Luke19:46\">LUK 19:45–19:46</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:14-John2:16\">JHN 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h3>Cursing the fig-tree</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:14\">MRK 11:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:19\">MAT 21:19</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's words in anger</h2>\n<h3>Against demons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:18\">MAT 17:18</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:25\">MRK 9:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:42\">LUK 9:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:25-Mark1:26\">MRK 1:25–1:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:35\">LUK 4:35</a></p>\n<h3>Against disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:55-Luke9:56\">LUK 9:55–9:56</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:23\">MAT 16:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:33\">MRK 8:33</a></p>\n<h3>Against Pharisees</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:13\">MAT 23:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:34\">MAT 12:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:7-Matt15:9\">MAT 15:7–15:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:6-Mark7:8\">MRK 7:6–7:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:15-Matt23:16\">MAT 23:15–23:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:23-Matt23:33\">MAT 23:23–23:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:42-Luke11:44\">LUK 11:42–11:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:15\">LUK 13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:44\">JHN 8:44</a></p>\n<h3>Against unbelief</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:17\">MAT 17:17</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:19\">MRK 9:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:41\">LUK 9:41</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:39-Matt12:45\">MAT 12:39–12:45</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:29-Luke11:32\">LUK 11:29–11:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:38\">MRK 8:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:50-Luke11:51\">LUK 11:50–11:51</a></p>\n<h3>Against false prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:15\">MAT 7:15</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Against the rich</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:24-Luke6:26\">LUK 6:24–6:26</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Against unrepentant cities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:20\">MAT 11:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:21-Matt11:24\">MAT 11:21–11:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:13-Luke10:15\">LUK 10:13–10:15</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ reflects the anger of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:36\">JHN 3:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:21-Matt5:22\">MAT 5:21–5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:29\">MAT 5:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:7\">MAT 22:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:13\">MAT 22:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:30\">MAT 25:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:46\">MAT 25:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:23\">LUK 21:23</a></p>\n<h2>The anger of the glorified Christ</h2>\n<h3>Against the unbelieving world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:16\">REV 6:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Against the wayward church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:16\">REV 2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:5\">REV 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:22-Rev2:23\">REV 2:22–2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:3\">REV 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:16\">REV 3:16</a></p>",
